O'FALLON CHAMBER OF COMMERCE: Providence Bank Announces Grand Opening Ceremonies for new Jefferson Ave Banking Center

Business

By Press release submission | Dec 3, 2018


Shutterstock

O'Fallon Chamber of Commerce issued the following announcement on Nov. 30.

Jen Megee, Executive Vice President, Director of Retail Banking and Deposit Services for Providence Bank is pleased to announce the Grand Opening of Providence Bank’s Jefferson Ave Banking Center. The new Jefferson Ave Banking Center is conveniently located at 1643 S. Jefferson Avenue in St. Louis, Missouri. The Banking Center features a night drop, safe deposit boxes and a drive-up image enabled depository ATM located in the parking lot for added convenience. The Banking Center is open Monday through Thursday from 8:30 am to 4:30 pm and on Friday from 8:30 am to 5:00 pm.

To celebrate the Grand Opening, Providence Bank is offering week-long special deals from Monday, December 3 to Friday, December 7. Special deals include two free gifts for opening a new checking account, CD Specials and other special offers! Visitors can also register to win a $100 Gift Card, Tickets to an event up to a $200 value and a Sharp 50-inch Ultra 4K LED Smart TV! On Friday, December 7, the bank will celebrate its official Grand Opening Day with extended hours from 8 am to 6 pm and by serving free pancakes from 8 am to 2 pm.

Jen Megee stated, “We are very excited to celebrate the Grand Opening of our new, convenient location! We invite everyone to join us for our grand opening festivities, take advantage of our special offers, tour our new state-of-the art banking center and register to win our prizes! Please stop by and celebrate with us.”

Providence Bank has been meeting the financial needs of individuals and businesses for more than 130 years. With the inclusion of this new office in St. Louis, Providence Bank has 14 banking centers serving clients in Columbia, Jefferson City, Osage Beach, St. Peters, St. Charles, Lake St. Louis, Elsberry and Winfield, Missouri; Fairview Heights, Illinois; and Premier Bank Texas, a full-service banking center in Grapevine, Texas. In addition, Providence Bank operates the Providence Bank Mortgage Center and Providence Bank Agency Finance. In addition to its office locations, Providence Bank provides anywhere, anytime financial services to customers via online banking, mobile banking and on its website at myprovidencebank.com. Providence Bank is a FDIC Member and Equal Housing Lender.

Original source can be found here.

Source: O'Fallon Chamber of Commerce
